157 bool MapStore::grow(int x, int y, int size) {
158  int newMinX = minX();
159  int xExpand = 0;
160  int delta = (x-size) - newMinX;
161  int xShift = 0;
162  if (delta < 0) {
163  xExpand = -delta;
164  xShift = xExpand;
165  newMinX = x-size;
166  }
167 
168  int newMaxX = maxX();
169  delta = (x+size) - newMaxX;
170  if (delta > 0) {
171  xExpand += delta;
172  newMaxX = x+size;
173  }
174 
175 
176  int newMinY = minY();
177  int yExpand = 0;
178  int yShift = 0;
179  delta = (y-size) - newMinY;
180  if (delta < 0) {
181  yExpand = -delta;
182  yShift = yExpand;
183  newMinY = y-size;
184  }
185 
186  int newMaxY = maxY();
187  delta = (y+size) - newMaxY;
188  if (delta > 0) {
189  yExpand += delta;
190  newMaxY = y+size;
191  }
192 
193  /* newMax - newMin must be even, otherwise expand one more. This is
194  * the case when Expand id even, because initially the difference is
195  * even. */
196  if (xExpand > 0) {
197  if (xExpand & 1) {
198  xExpand += 1;
199  newMaxX += 1;
200  }
201  }
202 
203  if (yExpand > 0) {
204  if (yExpand & 1) {
205  yExpand += 1;
206  newMaxY += 1;
207  }
208  }
209 
210  if (xExpand > 0 || yExpand > 0) {
211  int newSizeX = sizeX+xExpand;
212  int newSizeY = sizeY+yExpand;
213  double *newdata = new double[newSizeX*newSizeY];
214  int srcIdx = 0;
215  int destIdx = 0;
216  for (y=0; y < sizeY; y++) {
217  destIdx = (y+yShift)*newSizeX + xShift;
218  for (x=0; x < sizeX; x++) {
219  newdata[destIdx++] = data[srcIdx++];
220  }
221  }
222  delete[] data;
223  data = newdata;
224  maxIdx = newSizeX*newSizeY;
225  sizeX = newSizeX;
226  sizeY = newSizeY;
227  originX += xShift;
228  originY += yShift;
229  }
230  return true;
231 }

248 MapStoreTrace MapStore::trace(double x, double y, double dir, double length) const {
249  if (! (isInX(lround(x)) && isInY(lround(y))) )
250  throw MapStoreError(MapStoreError::Range);
251 
252  MapStoreBeam beamInfo(x, y, dir, length);
253 
254  MapStoreTrace result;
255 
256  int xIdx, yIdx;
257  beamInfo.getInitCell(xIdx, yIdx);
258  if (length > 0) {
259  do {
260  result.add(xIdx, yIdx, data[makeIdx(xIdx, yIdx)]);
261  } while (beamInfo.nextCell(xIdx, yIdx));
262  } else {
263  do {
264  result.add(xIdx, yIdx, data[makeIdx(xIdx, yIdx)]);
265  beamInfo.nextCell(xIdx, yIdx);

267  }

483 bool MapStore::loadMap(FILE *mapFH) {
484  enum loadStages {
485  lsSearchHeader,
486  lsMayFoundHeader,
487  lsInHeader,
488  lsSkipGP,
489  lsFoundData,
490  lsReadData,
491  lsDataOk,
492  lsDataFail
493  };
494 
495  bool headerPresent = false;
496 // bool headerComplete = false;
497 
498  // this could be put in struct, but since it is needed only once here, I used simple variables.
499  bool hasSize = false;
500  int mhSizeX;
501  int mhSizeY;
502  bool hasOrigin = false;
503  int mhOriginX;
504  int mhOriginY;
505  bool hasResolution = false;
506  double mhResolution;
507 
508  // progress through the file's sections
509  loadStages stage = lsSearchHeader;
510  bool badFile = false; // flag, set to true if format error detected.
511  bool readNext = true; // flag, true if a new line should be read.
512 
513  char *buffer = new char[8192];
514  char *pos = buffer;
515  int rowOffset = 0; // index into data array: start of current row.
516  int idx = 0; // character index into current line
517  int curRow = 0; // currently processed row
518 
519  while ( (!feof(mapFH)) && (stage != lsDataOk) && (stage != lsDataFail) && (badFile == false) ) {
520  if (readNext)
521  pos = fgets(buffer, 8190, mapFH);
522 
523  if (pos == 0)
524  break; // either error or end-of-file further check below
525 
526  if (pos[0] == '#')
527  continue; // comment line, skip it.
528 
529  switch (stage) {
530  case lsSearchHeader:
531  /* the header may have comments or empty lines before it.
532  * So this stage ends at the first non-empty line. */
533  idx = strspn(pos, " \t"); // first char not in list
534  if (pos[idx] == '\n') {
535  readNext = true; // empty line, skip it.
536  } else if (pos[0] == ' ') {
537  stage = lsFoundData; // starts with space, possible data row
538  readNext = false; // process data next round
539  } else {
540  stage = lsMayFoundHeader; // everything else is either a header line or visualization data.
541  readNext = false; // process data next round
542  }
543  break;
544 
545  case lsMayFoundHeader:
546  idx = strcspn(pos, ":");
547  if (idx > 0) {
548  // colon present, check text to its left
549  if (!strncmp(pos, "MapSize",idx)) {
550  // found header "MapSize"
551  stage = lsInHeader;
552  } else if (!strncmp(pos, "MapRes",idx)) {
553  // found header
554  stage = lsInHeader;
555  } else if (!strncmp(pos, "MapType",idx)) {
556  // found header
557  stage = lsInHeader;
558  } else if (!strncmp(pos, "MapOrigin",idx)) {
559  // found header
560  stage = lsInHeader;
561  } else {
562  // not a recognized header
563  stage =lsSkipGP;
564  }
565  } else {
566  // no colon, so not a header line
567  stage = lsSkipGP;
568  }
569  readNext = false; // process data next round
570  break;
571 
572  case lsInHeader:
573  idx = strcspn(pos, ":");
574  if (idx > 0) {
575  // colon present, check text to its left
576  if (!strncmp(pos, "MapSize", idx)) {
577  // found header "MapSize"
578  if (hasSize) {
579  // two size headers -> format error
580  badFile = true;
581  } else {
582  int conv = sscanf(&pos[idx+1], " %d %d", &mhSizeX, &mhSizeY);
583  if (conv != 2) {
584  badFile = true;
585  } else {
586  hasSize = true;
587  }
588  }
589  readNext = true; // done, next line
590  } else if (!strncmp(pos, "MapRes", idx)) {
591  // found header "MapRes"
592  if (hasResolution) {
593  // two resolution headers -> format error
594  badFile = true;
595  } else {
596  int conv = sscanf(&pos[idx+1], " %lf", &mhResolution);
597  if (conv != 1) {
598  badFile = true;
599  } else {
600  hasResolution = true;
601  }
602  }
603  readNext = true; // done, next line
604  } else if (!strncmp(pos, "MapType", idx)) {
605  // found header, do nothing
606  readNext = true; // done, next line
607  } else if (!strncmp(pos, "MapOrigin", idx)) {
608  // found header
609  if (hasOrigin) {
610  // two origin headers -> format error
611  badFile = true;
612  } else {
613  int conv = sscanf(&pos[idx+1], " %d %d", &mhOriginX, &mhOriginY);
614  if (conv != 2) {
615  badFile = true;
616  } else {
617  hasOrigin = true;
618  }
619  }
620  readNext = true; // done, next line
621  } else {
622  // not a recognized header
623  stage =lsSkipGP;
624 // headerComplete = true;
625  readNext = false; // process data next round
626  }
627  } else {
628  // no colon, so not a header line
629  stage = lsSkipGP;
630 // headerComplete = true;
631  readNext = false; // process data next round
632  }
633  break;
634 
635  case lsSkipGP:
636  /* the visualization info may have comments or empty lines
637  * in or before it.
638  * So this stage ends at the first line being a data line. */
639  idx = strspn(pos, " \t"); // first char not in list
640  if (pos[idx] == '\n') {
641  readNext = true; // empty line, skip it.
642  } else if (pos[0] == ' ') {
643  stage = lsFoundData; // starts with space, possible data row
644  readNext = false; // process data next round
645  } else {
646  // everything else is either a header line or visualization data.
647  // do nothing
648  }
649  break;
650 
651  case lsFoundData:
652  // first data row. check if we have all needed information to read it
653  headerPresent = hasSize || hasOrigin;
654  if (headerPresent && !hasSize) {
655  // size is mandatory if a header exists.
656  badFile = true;
657  break;
658  }
659  if (headerPresent) {
660  // header present, reset map.
661  delete[] data;
662  sizeX = mhSizeX | 1;
663  sizeY = mhSizeY | 1;
664  maxIdx = sizeX*sizeY;
665  data = new double[maxIdx];
666  if (hasOrigin) {
667  // mhOrigin is the cell coordinate that addresses the center of the map
668  originX = sizeX/2 - mhOriginX; // sizeX/2 = originX +mhOriginX
669  originY = sizeY/2 - mhOriginY;
670  } else {
671  // 0;0 is at map's center
672  originX = sizeX/2;
673  originY = sizeY/2;
674  }
675  if (hasResolution) {
676  resolution = mhResolution;
677  } else {
678  resolution = 1.0;
679  }
680  }
681 
682  stage = lsReadData;
683  readNext = false; // process data next round
684  break;
685 
686  case lsReadData:
687  if (pos[0] == 'e') {
688  stage = lsDataOk;
689  } else if (pos[0] == ' ') {
690  // data line
691  char *pnt = pos;
692  char *pnt2 = 0;
693  int i;
694 #ifdef DEBUG_LOAD
695  std::cout << "reading row " << curRow << " at offset " << rowOffset << std::endl;
696 #endif
697  for (i = 0; i < mhSizeX; i++) {
698  data[rowOffset+i] = strtod(pnt, &pnt2);
699  if (pnt2 == pnt) {
700  // conversion error
701  badFile = true;
702  stage = lsDataFail;
703  break;
704  }
705  pnt = pnt2;
706  }
707  // here pnt2 must be at the end of the line and i must be mhSizeX
708  idx = strspn(pnt2, " \t");
709  if (pnt2[idx] != '\n') {
710  // garbage after data
711  badFile = true;
712  stage = lsDataFail;
713  }
714  if (i != mhSizeX) {
715  // short line
716  badFile = true;
717  stage = lsDataFail;
718  }
719  rowOffset += sizeX;
720  curRow += 1;
721  if (curRow == mhSizeY)
722  stage = lsDataOk;
723 
724  readNext = true;
725  } else {
726  // format error
727  badFile = true;
728  stage = lsDataFail;
729  }
730  break;
731 
732  case lsDataOk:
733 #ifdef DEBUG_LOAD
734  std::cout << "lsDataOk reached" << std::endl;
735  break;
736 #endif
737  // fall through
738  case lsDataFail:
739  // do nothing, while () will terminate.
740 #ifdef DEBUG_LOAD
741  std::cout << "lsDataFail reached" << std::endl;
742 #endif
743  break;
744  }
745  } // end of while
746  delete[] buffer;
747  if (stage == lsDataFail)
748  throw MapStoreError(MapStoreError::Format);
749 #ifdef DEBUG_LOAD
750  std::cout << "badFile is " << ((badFile == true) ? "true" : "false") << std::endl;
751 #endif
752  return(!badFile);
753 }
